claim.claim-text:
1. An apparatus worn by a user for carrying a pet comprising:
a. a shirt with sleeves worn on a torso of a user;
b. a pouch having an open end attached on a first side of said shirt; wherein the pet is received through said open end and retained within said pouch;
c. said pouch having a single vertically extending pleat centrally located in a front wall of said pouch for allowing expansion of said pouch;
d. means for restraining said pet within said pouch comprising a first fastener selected from the group consisting of a drawstring, snaps, zippers, and hook and loop fasteners to fasten the first open end of the pouch; and
e. a mesh window for pet viewing and ventilation, said mesh window being between said open end of said pouch and said pleat.
